Behavior summarized:
- MCP builtin lifecycle handlers are wrapped through the existing async guard path.
- McpService now owns process-backed server connections across session starts.
- Session shutdown with reason "new" keeps matching server connections alive.
- Session shutdown with reason "reload" or "quit" disposes process-owned connections.
- Config-hash changes replace only the changed server connection.
- Disabled and untrusted project servers are not spawned.
- Tool registration preserves the intended active tool set after MCP tools auto-register.

